WEBVTT

00:01.044 --> 00:02.698
Robin Randall was

00:02.741 --> 00:04.700
a stay-at-home
suburban mother of two,

00:04.743 --> 00:08.443
living 14 years free and clear
of any criminal activity,

00:08.486 --> 00:11.272
when, all of a sudden,
she returns to the hotbed

00:11.315 --> 00:14.014
of delinquency from her past --
New York City,

00:14.057 --> 00:17.191
home of 12,000 security cameras
pointed straight at you.

00:17.234 --> 00:18.670
Did you really think
you could go by unnoticed?

00:18.714 --> 00:20.324
-What was in the bag?
-What bag?

00:22.674 --> 00:24.285
Oh.
The...bag.

00:24.328 --> 00:26.983
I don't -- It's -- I lost it,
so it doesn't matter.

00:27.027 --> 00:28.332
You can stall all you want,

00:28.376 --> 00:29.899
but the guy we've got
in the next room --

00:29.942 --> 00:31.074
he's telling us everything.

00:31.118 --> 00:32.380
[ Click ]

00:32.423 --> 00:34.121
This guy -- I know him.
Her. I know him.

00:34.164 --> 00:36.819
She -- I don't know.
I have no idea who she is.

00:36.862 --> 00:38.342
I don't know who that is.
Or that.

00:38.386 --> 00:40.562
Or that. Or that.
Or tha--

00:40.605 --> 00:42.216
Talk to me
about your husband.

00:42.259 --> 00:44.914
Uh, well, Nate has nothing
to do with any of this.

00:44.957 --> 00:46.089
She was talking about this guy.

00:46.133 --> 00:47.134
[ Click ]

00:47.177 --> 00:49.353
Carlos is it?

00:50.615 --> 00:51.703
[ Horn honks ]

00:55.620 --> 00:56.665
Nate:
What time is it?

00:56.708 --> 00:57.753
What?
Oh, it's early.

00:57.796 --> 00:59.059
Where are you going?

00:59.102 --> 01:00.408
-Go back to sleep, babe.
-Why are you up?

01:00.451 --> 01:02.062
It's just I-I'm gonna
run out real quick.

01:02.105 --> 01:03.715
-Okay.
-Okay.

01:03.759 --> 01:05.152
-Get me a bagel.
-Hmm? Yeah.

01:05.195 --> 01:06.631
With...poppies.
And a coffee.

01:06.675 --> 01:07.806
Okay.

01:07.850 --> 01:08.981
And don't go
to the close place.

01:09.025 --> 01:10.548
Go to the good place.
-Bye.

01:10.592 --> 01:11.854
-And a milk and coffee.
-Okay. Milk and coffee.

01:11.897 --> 01:13.247
[ Door closes ]

01:13.290 --> 01:15.118
[ Urinating ]

01:18.382 --> 01:19.601
Babe?

01:19.644 --> 01:22.343
You back already?

01:22.386 --> 01:24.519
Hey, did I say "poppy,"
'cause I meant "everything."

01:24.562 --> 01:26.782
Did you get me everything?
'Cause I wanted everything.

01:26.825 --> 01:28.740
Where are my glasses?

01:28.784 --> 01:30.786
Uh, how should I know?

01:30.829 --> 01:33.354
What? What's wrong
with your voice?

01:33.397 --> 01:36.270
What's wrong
with your face?

01:36.313 --> 01:38.707
What?

01:43.015 --> 01:44.887
You got my shirt on?

01:44.930 --> 01:47.150
Uh, yeah.
I was cold.

01:50.893 --> 01:52.024
Babe?

01:52.068 --> 01:53.069
The pig?

01:53.113 --> 01:54.810
-Oh, shit.
-Back off, perv!

01:54.853 --> 01:56.377
Aah!
What -- [ Coughs ]

01:56.420 --> 01:58.161
Check your
privacy settings.

01:58.205 --> 02:00.032
[ Coughs ]
What the hell?!

02:00.076 --> 02:01.382
Who are you?

02:01.425 --> 02:03.123
-I'm Hannah.
-What are you doing here?!

02:03.166 --> 02:05.473
Uh, I ate dan-dan noodles
and I did a mound of coke.

02:05.516 --> 02:06.952
What do you think
I'm doing?

02:06.996 --> 02:08.302
[ Laughing ] Wait.
Hold on.

02:08.345 --> 02:09.955
You look like the old guy
from "Up."

02:09.999 --> 02:11.000
Here.
One second.

02:11.043 --> 02:12.523
Um, be grumpy.

02:12.567 --> 02:13.655
What?[ Camera shutter clicks ]

02:13.698 --> 02:14.830
Perfect.

02:14.873 --> 02:16.092
Why are you
in my apartment?

02:16.136 --> 02:18.181
-Oh, this is your place?
-Yes.

02:18.225 --> 02:19.835
-How much do you pay?
-A lot.

02:19.878 --> 02:21.532
Well, hopefully
not too much.

02:21.576 --> 02:22.968
You have ghosts.

02:23.012 --> 02:26.755
Let me start again.
Why are you here?

02:26.798 --> 02:28.191
I came with Paris.

02:28.235 --> 02:29.497
Who's Paris?

02:29.540 --> 02:31.107
-She's friends with Bean.
-Who's Bean?

02:31.151 --> 02:32.891
[ Laughing ] Oh, my God.
He's so chill.

02:32.935 --> 02:35.503
Actually,
could you do me a favor?

02:35.546 --> 02:37.896
Could you tell me
you're proud of me?

02:37.940 --> 02:39.637
-Why?
-It helps me go.

02:39.681 --> 02:42.510
Finish up whatever disgusting
thing you're doing right now

02:42.553 --> 02:43.902
and get out of my house.

02:46.383 --> 02:49.517
Oh.
What -- What are you?

02:49.560 --> 02:51.214
Are you Paris
or are you Bean?

02:51.258 --> 02:53.347
[ Crying ]
Are you mad at me, Daddy?

02:53.390 --> 02:55.305
Yes,
I'm very mad at you.

02:55.349 --> 02:56.654
I need you out of here.

02:56.698 --> 02:58.439
And I'm not that old,
okay?

02:58.482 --> 03:00.049
[ Straining ]
Oh, my God.

03:00.092 --> 03:02.356
Oh, geez.

03:02.399 --> 03:03.922
Ew.

03:03.966 --> 03:05.576
Whoa!

03:10.407 --> 03:12.235
What the hell is going on
in here?!

03:12.279 --> 03:13.410
Shit.
Sorry, Nate.

03:13.454 --> 03:15.195
I'm sorry.
I told them to be quiet.

03:15.238 --> 03:16.718
Hey, the guy from "Up."

03:16.761 --> 03:18.110
-Who are you?
-I'm Bean.

03:18.154 --> 03:19.460
This is Carlos.

03:19.503 --> 03:21.375
Stop saying names of people
I don't know!

03:21.418 --> 03:23.899
Carlos. "The guy who I helped
get his green card" Carlos.

03:23.942 --> 03:25.074
Ex-husband Carlos.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.989
No "ex."
Current-husband Carlos.

03:27.032 --> 03:28.730
Mucho gusto, señor.

03:28.773 --> 03:30.645
It's nice the three of us
could finally meet.

03:30.688 --> 03:32.081
I just re-grammed you.

03:32.124 --> 03:33.256
You get the...away
from me.

03:33.300 --> 03:35.563
Oh, my God!

03:35.606 --> 03:37.042
Ow!

03:37.086 --> 03:38.609
Get out!

03:38.653 --> 03:41.264
♪ Somewhere behind the skyline

03:41.308 --> 03:43.788
♪ There is a place
I'm thinkin' ♪

03:43.832 --> 03:47.052
[ Distorted music plays ]

03:50.317 --> 03:51.666
You said
he was short and fat.

03:51.709 --> 03:53.102
No, I didn't.

03:53.145 --> 03:54.451
I said you didn't need
to be threatened by him.

03:54.495 --> 03:56.801
Well, I'm not,
but...in my current state...

03:56.845 --> 03:58.760
Yeah, what's going on
with this?

03:58.803 --> 03:59.978
Oh, I don't know.

04:00.022 --> 04:01.241
I got talc'ed
by the Hooters waitress.

04:01.284 --> 04:02.372
-Who?
-Why is he here?

04:02.416 --> 04:03.939
Why are you here?
-He found my bag.

04:03.982 --> 04:05.332
-What bag?
-The bag.

04:05.375 --> 04:06.942
How did you find the bag?

04:06.985 --> 04:08.422
I was in a bus station,
coming home from Miami.

04:08.465 --> 04:10.337
You took a bus
from "My-jammy."

04:10.380 --> 04:12.295
Sí.
It's the only way to travel.

04:12.339 --> 04:14.950
I hear the bus driver yelling,
"Robin Randall!

04:14.993 --> 04:16.386
Robin Randall, your bag!"

04:16.430 --> 04:17.996
Let me get this straight.

04:18.040 --> 04:20.303
In a city of 8 million people,
you just happened

04:20.347 --> 04:22.479
to be walking by the bag
of your fake wife

04:22.523 --> 04:24.133
you haven't seen
in 14 years.

04:24.176 --> 04:26.527
Sí. That kind of stuff
happens to me all the time.

04:26.570 --> 04:28.224
-Where's the bag?
-It's at the club.

04:28.268 --> 04:29.878
-What?
-I was gonna go get it,

04:29.921 --> 04:31.401
but then everybody had to use
the bathroom, so here we are.

04:31.445 --> 04:33.447
You guys should really
sublet this kitchen.

04:33.490 --> 04:35.187
It's so much nicer than
the kitchen I'm living in.

04:35.231 --> 04:36.624
Why didn't you
bring it here?

04:36.667 --> 04:37.929
Because I knew she would
want to see the club.

04:37.973 --> 04:39.322
Why would you want
to see the club?

04:39.366 --> 04:40.628
Listen, Nate, I've been
over this with him.

04:40.671 --> 04:41.977
Trust me --
it's just gonna be easier

04:42.020 --> 04:43.457
if I go to the club
and get the bag.

04:43.500 --> 04:45.372
Okay. Fine. Take Phi Beta
Brooklyn with you.

04:45.415 --> 04:47.504
[ Beep, man laughs ]

04:47.548 --> 04:50.028
[ Tito Nieves'
"I Like It Like That" plays ]Nice choice, Frijole.

04:50.072 --> 04:51.595
Hey, it's Bean.
And you told me to play this.

04:51.639 --> 04:53.118
Turn this off.

04:53.162 --> 04:54.642
Oh, it's mí and mí esposa's
wedding song.

04:54.685 --> 04:56.078
♪ I like it like that

04:56.121 --> 04:58.298
♪ Yeah, baby

04:58.341 --> 04:59.299
♪ I like it like that

04:59.342 --> 05:00.604
[ Laughs ]

05:00.648 --> 05:02.432
Yeah...song for your
green-card wedding?

05:02.476 --> 05:03.564
Yeah, we had to make it
look real.

05:03.607 --> 05:04.565
Who makes this
their song?

05:04.608 --> 05:05.740
♪ I got soul

05:05.783 --> 05:08.873
People who like it like this.

05:08.917 --> 05:10.222
-Hey, hey!
-Hey.

05:10.266 --> 05:12.137
-Hey, hey!
-No, Nate! Nate!

05:12.181 --> 05:13.704
No. No, no, no.

05:13.748 --> 05:15.184
What the hell is going on?![ Beep, music stops ]

05:15.227 --> 05:16.664
Trust me.
I'm just as confused as you are.

05:16.707 --> 05:18.143
These are your niños?

05:18.187 --> 05:20.276
[ Laughs ]
So big.

05:20.320 --> 05:24.367
This one --
she looks like her father.

05:24.411 --> 05:27.022
But this one -- special.

05:27.065 --> 05:28.763
Your name, muchachito.

05:28.806 --> 05:30.068
It's Jareb.

05:30.112 --> 05:32.680
Yareb.

05:32.723 --> 05:35.552
You know, Yareb, your mother
and I used to dance

05:35.596 --> 05:37.685
during our long nights
of excess.

05:37.728 --> 05:39.251
-What'd you say?
-He said "excess."

05:39.295 --> 05:40.992
-No, he didn't.
-His accent made it sound

05:41.036 --> 05:42.429
like he said something else.
-Every other word was fine.

05:42.472 --> 05:44.082
Why did he stumble on that?
-I don't know.

05:44.126 --> 05:45.388
And what are these long nights
he's talking about?

05:45.432 --> 05:46.911
Just parties --
I mean, occasionally.

05:46.955 --> 05:48.217
You know.
-I don't know.

05:48.260 --> 05:49.827
-I don't do that.
-Yes, you did.

05:49.871 --> 05:51.438
Petirroja
can be very coy.

05:51.481 --> 05:54.049
-What did you call her?
-It means "red breast."

05:54.092 --> 05:56.704
-It's like the bird robin.
-Robin the bird.

05:56.747 --> 05:58.053
-Yeah.
-Sí. Bird.

05:58.096 --> 06:01.491
[ Laughs ]
Brrr-brrr-brrrr.

06:01.535 --> 06:02.797
[ Laughs ]
Brrr-brrr-brrrr.

06:02.840 --> 06:06.366
[ Laughter ]

06:06.409 --> 06:08.193
It's a shitty bird impression.

06:08.237 --> 06:09.978
Okay.
I'm gonna go get the bag.

06:10.021 --> 06:11.240
I'll be back in an hour.

06:11.283 --> 06:12.546
An hour? No, no.
I got to go to work.

06:12.589 --> 06:13.677
You take the kids.

06:13.721 --> 06:15.462
I can't take the kids
to the club.

06:15.505 --> 06:16.854
-We're fine on our own, guys.
-No, honey, you're not fine.

06:16.898 --> 06:18.595
One hour. I'll -- I'll
meet you at work, okay?

06:18.639 --> 06:19.683
It's gonna be fine.

06:19.727 --> 06:20.989
[ Claps hands ]
Come on.

06:21.032 --> 06:22.643
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

06:22.686 --> 06:23.992
Come on, come on, come on,
come on, come on, come on.

06:24.035 --> 06:25.689
Come on, come on.
-Let's go.

06:25.733 --> 06:26.821
It's fine,
it's fine, it's fine.

06:26.864 --> 06:28.300
What the hell
just happened?

06:33.654 --> 06:36.221
I don't understand why we
can't just explore the city.

06:36.265 --> 06:37.832
Don't blame me.
Blame your mom.

06:37.875 --> 06:39.399
So -- so,
can we take off?

06:39.442 --> 06:41.139
No. I want you guys
to come see my new job.

06:41.183 --> 06:42.489
What do you do?

06:42.532 --> 06:44.316
I sell structured
hydro-nutrients.

06:44.360 --> 06:46.449
-Isn't that just water?
-Are you kidding me?

06:46.493 --> 06:48.669
We are harnessing
its innate chemical memory

06:48.712 --> 06:50.671
to optimize axon functions
in the brain,

06:50.714 --> 06:52.847
which keep the body clear
of harmful toxins

06:52.890 --> 06:54.762
and promote
and sustain mood balance.

06:54.805 --> 06:56.677
Now, does that sound
like just water?

06:56.720 --> 06:59.810
-Yes.
-It...it's not.

06:59.854 --> 07:01.812
So, pretty great, huh?

07:01.856 --> 07:03.205
It's empty.

07:03.248 --> 07:04.598
Yeah, I know.
I'm the first of many.

07:04.641 --> 07:06.338
It seems creepy.

07:06.382 --> 07:08.471
Guys, would you please just
give me something here?

07:08.515 --> 07:09.864
It's pretty awesome.

07:09.907 --> 07:11.300
I got a corner office
and everything.

07:11.343 --> 07:12.693
It's kind of cool.

07:12.736 --> 07:15.957
No, it's damn cool.
I'm the boss.

07:16.000 --> 07:17.785
It's cool.
Can we go?

07:17.828 --> 07:19.264
Yeah, where's mom?

07:19.308 --> 07:21.528
I...don't have a watch.

07:21.571 --> 07:24.487
And no.
Come on.

07:24.531 --> 07:27.229
[ Dance music playing,
indistinct conversations ]

07:32.539 --> 07:33.757
Thank you for that.

07:33.801 --> 07:35.324
It still would have been
so much easier

07:35.367 --> 07:37.152
just to leave it
with the bus company.

07:37.195 --> 07:38.414
So, this is the part

07:38.458 --> 07:40.329
where I ask you what
you're really up to.

07:40.372 --> 07:42.592
I'm just happy
to be of service.

07:42.636 --> 07:46.117
And very happy to see you
so happy in an otherwise...

07:46.161 --> 07:48.206
how do you say...
dull life.

07:48.250 --> 07:50.687
[ Laughing ] Okay.
Nice try on the neg.

07:50.731 --> 07:53.995
You have your bag,
your beautiful children,

07:54.038 --> 07:56.693
your strapping man,
his new job.

07:56.737 --> 07:59.174
You should go.

07:59.217 --> 08:01.045
That's the reverse neg.

08:01.089 --> 08:02.090
That's -- that's original.

08:02.133 --> 08:03.395
Do you mean a compliment?

08:03.439 --> 08:05.702
Ugh!
This place.

08:05.746 --> 08:08.923
What are we?
Like...22? Come on.

08:08.966 --> 08:10.577
-It feels that way.
-Yeah, it doesn't.

08:15.625 --> 08:17.366
I'm leaving.

08:23.720 --> 08:25.461
[ Beep ]Babe, where are you?

08:25.505 --> 08:27.376
It's been two hours.
I'm worried.

08:27.419 --> 08:31.119
Give me a call.

08:31.162 --> 08:33.730
[ Sighs ]

08:33.774 --> 08:38.082
[ Dance music playing ]

08:38.126 --> 08:41.782
iPetirroja!
You are a vision.

08:41.825 --> 08:43.261
39 years old, two kids,

08:43.305 --> 08:45.699
and I can still rock
a size-zero dress.

08:45.742 --> 08:47.788
Suck it, Millennials.
Right?

08:47.831 --> 08:49.485
So basic.

08:53.576 --> 08:55.665
[ Ringing ]

08:55.709 --> 08:57.537
Hannah:
Why are you calling me?

08:57.580 --> 08:58.799
I have to work tonight.

08:58.842 --> 09:00.452
-Who is this?
-It's Hannah.

09:00.496 --> 09:02.411
You're still at my house?
What...

09:02.454 --> 09:03.978
Okay.
Uh, is my wife there?

09:04.021 --> 09:06.023
No.

09:06.067 --> 09:07.503
Hey, that club
you guys were at --

09:07.547 --> 09:08.635
it's not listed anywhere.
Do you know where it is?

09:08.678 --> 09:11.028
-Yeah.
-Well, where is it?

09:11.072 --> 09:12.247
I can't tell you.

09:12.290 --> 09:13.422
Why not?

09:13.465 --> 09:15.293
Because
I have to show you.

09:15.337 --> 09:16.991
Fine. Listen, you guys
want to stay here?

09:17.034 --> 09:18.819
Okay. Play on your phones.
I'll be back in 20 minutes.

09:18.862 --> 09:20.472
Hannah, stay there.
I'm coming to get you.

09:20.516 --> 09:22.170
Don't do anything stupid, okay?
Thank you.

09:22.213 --> 09:23.606
Well, you might have
to sleep with Carlos

09:23.650 --> 09:24.781
to get into the club.

09:26.827 --> 09:27.958
Aah!

09:28.002 --> 09:29.525
You all right, dad?

09:29.569 --> 09:30.700
Yep.
All good.

09:35.531 --> 09:36.924
You guys the new recruits?

09:36.967 --> 09:38.708
No.
We're Nate Parker's kids.

09:38.752 --> 09:41.058
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, I figured.

09:41.102 --> 09:42.451
I was just, uh...

09:42.494 --> 09:44.932
So, uh, where's your dad?

09:44.975 --> 09:46.237
He went to get my mom.

09:46.281 --> 09:48.326
Great!
Can't wait to see her.

09:48.370 --> 09:50.851
So, uh, what do you think
of your dad's new job?

09:50.894 --> 09:52.287
He's the boss.

09:52.330 --> 09:55.333
Gonna be selling
structured hydro-nutrients.

09:55.377 --> 09:57.205
They're what happens
to water when --

09:57.248 --> 09:58.641
Yeah.
We read the pamphlet.

09:58.685 --> 10:00.948
You know, I don't get you kids.

10:00.991 --> 10:05.343
You got three whole floors of
empty, raw space, no parents,

10:05.387 --> 10:07.607
no rules, and all you're doing
is sitting on your --

10:07.650 --> 10:09.391
Hey, uh, dude, Wi-Fi --
what's the password?

10:09.434 --> 10:14.048
Oh.
Um, I'll go check on that.

10:15.919 --> 10:18.139
What a weirdo.

10:27.365 --> 10:28.628
Hey.

10:29.280 --> 10:30.891
[ Sighs ]

10:31.543 --> 10:33.545
I got your Wi-Fi password.

10:38.115 --> 10:40.161
-So cool!
-That was awesome!

10:40.204 --> 10:42.816
Put your damn phones down,
and I'll let you try it.

10:42.859 --> 10:45.601
All right, I'm out of here.
You know why?

10:45.645 --> 10:48.473
'Cause I am a good,
responsible mother now.

10:48.517 --> 10:53.565
I got to go pick up, uh...
what's her name and that boy.

10:53.609 --> 10:56.394
Okay. I guess this is...
how do you say...

10:56.438 --> 10:58.875
adios.

10:58.919 --> 11:00.703
[ Laughing ] Okay.
Yeah, that's good.
That's original.

11:00.747 --> 11:03.140
This guy -- all he ever wants
is to get into my pants.

11:03.184 --> 11:04.881
But you know what, pal?
Not anymore.

11:04.925 --> 11:06.448
'Cause this gal is taken.

11:06.491 --> 11:07.797
-So am I.
-What?

11:07.841 --> 11:08.972
Oh.

11:09.016 --> 11:11.714
Robin, Sophia.

11:11.758 --> 11:13.760
Sophia...Robin.

11:13.803 --> 11:16.153
Oh. Oh.
Oh.

11:16.197 --> 11:17.546
The jealousy play.

11:17.589 --> 11:19.461
[ Laughing ] Oh!
Not!

11:19.504 --> 11:23.508
That's...
Come up for air much?

11:23.552 --> 11:25.554
Hey, junior high called.

11:25.597 --> 11:27.382
Your braces are getting
locked together.

11:27.425 --> 11:30.907
You're so hungry.
Eat a sandwich.

